<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>The New Work Times</title>
 <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.5/css/bootstrap.min.css">
  <script type="text/javascript" src=" https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.5/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body>

<div class="mymodal">	
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
        <h4 class="modal-title">What is The New Work Times?</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>If you’re an average reader, I’ve got your attention for 15 seconds. Ads, multimedia items and links push you to leave the page that you're reading every second making concentrating on a single text a hard job.
        What if you could copy and paste the URL of the page you are reading and get back a proper, essential and clean page with the text you were reading?!
		<br />
		<br />
		This is the way you can read and save articles on The New Work Times.</p>
      </div>
    </div><!-- /.modal-content -->
  </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->
</div>

<script>
$('.close').on('click', function(event) {
		event.preventDefault();
		$('.mymodal').hide();
	});
</script>

</body>
</html>